From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Mar 2026 11:02:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] drm: panel-mipi stop double-registering orientation

The temporary connector-side orientation registration now collides with
the panel get_orientation callback, producing boot-time DRM warnings on
RG35XX SP. Keep the panel callback and drop the temporary fallback.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-mipi.c | 5 -----
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-mipi.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-mipi.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-mipi.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-mipi.c
@@ -922,12 +922,6 @@ static int panel_mipi_get_modes(struct drm_panel *panel,
 	drm_display_info_set_bus_formats(&connector->display_info,
 					 &mipi->bus_format, 1);
 
-	/*
-	 * TODO: Remove once all drm drivers call
-	 * drm_connector_set_orientation_from_panel()
-	 */
-	drm_connector_set_panel_orientation(connector, mipi->orientation);
-
 	return count;
 }
 
-- 
2.49.0
